      "content": "You may want to check for carbon deposits in the spark plug holes, potentially clogging injector nozzles, or related components in the fuel delivery system. Also, consider checking the oxygen sensors, as a malfunctioning ones can cause lean conditions. If you're comfortable, you could also inspect for vacuum leaks since they might also lead to a lean condition. Each component can impact the fuel-to-air ratio, so these may help you isolate the cause. However, if the issues persist, consulting a professional may be a wise decision.",
